{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1772139003,"nonce":"kg3128TVWs4bow7iQgIDhi3ryfc=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87uR91O","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/295","origin":"github"},"title":"Add tidal water level to asv_sim and mbes_sim for tide detector validation","message":"## Summary\n\nAdd a tidal water level model to `asv_sim` and `mbes_sim` so the simulator produces\nplausible vertical variation. This enables end-to-end validation of the\n`sea_surface_estimator` tide detector in `mru_transform`.\n\nCurrently:\n- `asv_sim` is purely 2D — `NavSatFix.altitude` is never set (defaults to 0.0)\n- `mbes_sim` reads depths from the bathymetric grid with no water level offset\n- `sea_surface_estimator` averages `odom.pose.pose.position.z`, which is always ~0\n\n## Approach\n\n### Tide model in `asv_sim` (environment.py)\n\nAdd a harmonic tide model to `Environment`. A simplified model using the top 3\nconstituents from NOAA Station 8423898 (Fort Point, NH — Portsmouth Harbor) would\nproduce a plausible signal:\n\n| Constituent | Amplitude (m) | Speed (°/hr) | Phase GMT (°) |\n|-------------|---------------|--------------|---------------|\n| M2          | 1.295         | 28.984       | 105.6         |\n| N2          | 0.289         | 28.440       | 73.4          |\n| S2          | 0.197         | 30.000       | 142.1         |\n\nThe tide height above MLLW at time _t_ (hours since midnight UTC) is:\n```\nh(t) = Σ Aᵢ · cos(speedᵢ · t − phaseᵢ)\n```\n\nDefault parameters should produce the Portsmouth Harbor signal (~2.6 m mean range),\nbut all constituent parameters should be configurable via ROS parameters under\n`environment.tide.*` so other locations can be simulated.\n\nA simpler option: a single `environment.tide.amplitude` and `environment.tide.period`\nfor a basic sinusoidal tide, with the multi-constituent model as a stretch goal.\n\n### Ellipsoidal height reference\n\nReal GPS outputs WGS84 ellipsoidal height, not orthometric or tidal datum height.\nFrom [VDatum](https://vdatum.noaa.gov/) at Portsmouth Harbor (43.072°N, 70.711°W):\n\n| Quantity | Value |\n|----------|-------|\n| NAD83/WGS84 ellipsoid to MLLW | −28.104 m |\n| Uncertainty | ±0.111 m |\n\nSo the simulated `NavSatFix.altitude` should be:\n```\naltitude = ellipsoid_to_mllw + tide_above_mllw\n         = -28.104 + h(t)\n```\n\nWhere `h(t)` is the harmonic tide height above MLLW.\n\n`mru_transform` sets its map origin at ellipsoidal altitude 0.0\n(`mru_transform.cpp:59`), so the local z in odom will be the difference from that\norigin. This means the *absolute* ellipsoidal height doesn't affect the tide\ndetector's behavior — only the variation matters. But outputting proper ellipsoidal\nheight is correct practice and matters for any downstream code that uses the raw\nNavSatFix.\n\nA configurable `environment.tide.ellipsoid_to_mllw` parameter (default: −28.104)\nallows different locations. This value can be obtained from VDatum for any US\ncoastal location.\n\n### Propagate altitude through asv_sim\n\n- Add `altitude` state variable to `dynamics.py`\n- Set `altitude = ellipsoid_to_mllw + tide_height(t)` on each update (surface vessel tracks water level)\n- Populate `NavSatFix.altitude` in `platform.py` (`nsf.altitude = self.dynamics.altitude`)\n- The existing `mru_transform` pipeline already converts `NavSatFix.altitude` → ECEF → local z → `odom.pose.pose.position.z`, so no changes needed there\n\n### Apply tide offset in mbes_sim\n\nThe default bathymetry grid (`US5NH02M.tiff`) is a NOAA chart raster, likely referenced\nto MLLW. With a tide offset, the water depth becomes:\n\n```\ndepth_actual = depth_chart + tide_above_mllw\n```\n\nThis means when tide is high, measured depth increases; when tide is low, it decreases.\n\nChanges to `mbes_sim.py`:\n- Accept a `water_level` or subscribe to a tide topic (published by `asv_sim`)\n- Apply offset to grid depths before publishing\n\n**Design choice**: Should `mbes_sim` compute tide independently (duplicating the model)\nor subscribe to a shared tide topic from `asv_sim`? A shared topic\n(`environment/tide_level`, `Float64`) is cleaner — single source of truth, and useful\nfor other nodes that may need water level.\n\n### Datum context (for reference, not implementation)\n\nFrom [NOAA Station 8423898](https://tidesandcurrents.noaa.gov/datums.html?id=8423898) (Fort Point, NH):\n\n| Datum | Feet above MLLW | Meters |\n|-------|-----------------|--------|\n| MHHW  | 9.39            | 2.86   |\n| MHW   | 8.97            | 2.73   |\n| MSL   | 4.69            | 1.43   |\n| NAVD88| 5.00            | 1.52   |\n| MLW   | 0.34            | 0.10   |\n| MLLW  | 0.00            | 0.00   |\n\nMean range (MN): 8.63 ft / 2.63 m. Great diurnal range (GT): 9.39 ft / 2.86 m.\n\nFor the simulator, an `environment.tide.datum_offset` parameter could shift the\nreference (e.g., set to 1.43 to work relative to MSL instead of MLLW), but this\nis a nice-to-have.\n\n## Packages affected\n\n- `asv_sim` — tide model + altitude propagation (`unh_marine_simulation` repo)\n- `mbes_sim` — water level offset on depths (`unh_marine_simulation` repo)\n- Config files (new tide parameters in platform YAML configs)\n\n## Validation\n\nOnce implemented:\n1. Launch simulation with default Portsmouth Harbor tide parameters\n2. Observe `odom.pose.pose.position.z` varying over time (~±1.3 m)\n3. Observe `sea_surface_estimator` producing a `map_tide` transform that tracks the tide\n4. Observe `mbes_sim` depth values varying with tide (e.g., ±1.3 m from chart depth)\n5. Compare `map_tide` z against known tide input to characterize estimator lag/accuracy\n\n## References\n\n- [NOAA Station 8423898 datums](https://tidesandcurrents.noaa.gov/datums.html?id=8423898)\n- [NOAA Station 8423898 harmonic constituents (API)](https://api.tidesandcurrents.noaa.gov/mdapi/prod/webapi/stations/8423898/harcon.json?units=metric)\n- [VDatum vertical datum transformation tool](https://vdatum.noaa.gov/)\n- `sea_surface_estimator`: `mru_transform/nodes/sea_surface_estimator.cpp`\n- `mru_transform` map origin: `mru_transform/src/mru_transform.cpp:56-61` (altitude set to 0.0)\n- `mru_transform` position→odom: `mru_transform/src/map_frame.cpp:59-65` (GeoPoint→ECEF→local)\n- `asv_sim` platform: `asv_sim/asv_sim/platform.py:154-161` (NavSatFix, no altitude)\n- `asv_sim` environment: `asv_sim/asv_sim/environment.py` (currents only, no tide)\n- `mbes_sim` depth: `mbes_sim/mbes_sim/mbes_sim.py:137-144` (raw grid depth)\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: `Claude Code Agent`\n**Model**: `Claude Opus 4.6`","files":null}]}